Step 4: Configure Hosts File

vi /etc/ansible/hosts

[ansiblegroup]
<private_ip_of_node1>
<private_ip_of_node2>

Step 5: Create User

adduser devops

password: devops (press enter 3 times, then y)

Same username/password across all machines


Step 6:Configure SSH

vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config

#Line 34 → PermitRootLogin yes

#Line 47 → remove #

#Line 66 → PasswordAuthentication yes

On Ubuntu 24.04 also edit:

cd /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/
ls

sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/60-cloudimg-settings.conf

#Set PasswordAuthentication yes

service ssh restart

Same thing node1 and node2 also

####then go back to master

Step 7:Grant Sudo Privileges

Run "visudo" on master nodes
Add:
devops ALL=(ALL:ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL

Step 8: Establish SSH Trust

su - devops
ssh-keygen   # press enter 3 times
ls -a
cd .ssh

ssh-copy-id devops@<private_ip_of_node1>
ssh-copy-id devops@<private_ip_of_node2>


Enter password (devops) when prompted.

Now master can connect to nodes without password

Step 9: Verify Setup

ansible all -m ping -i /etc/ansible/hosts

ansible all -a"touch file"
